          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Bk-249 was produced of seven targets, containing",
                "approx. 50 g of actinides, predominately Cm (42 g),",
                "Am (5 g) and Pu (3 g)",
                "Six targets were manufactured from this material, by",
                "depositing BkO(2) oxide onto 0.74 mg/cm**2 Ti foils to",
                "a thickness of 0.31 mg/cm**2 of Bk-249. Each target had",
                "an area of 6.0 cm**2 in the shape of an arc segment",
                "with an angular extension of 60 deg and an average",
                "radius of 60 mm.",
                "In the course of the bombardment with an intense beam",
                "of Ca-48, the target layers of BkO(2) were",
                "systematically monitored by counting particles from the",
                "decay of Cf-249, the beta-decay daughter of Bk-249Bk.",
                "At the start of the experiment 37 mug/cm**2 of the",
                "Cf-249 daughter was present in the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  a 4-cm*12-cm semiconductor detector array with",
                "12 vertical position-sensitive strips surrounded by",
                "eight 4-cm*4-cm side detectors without position",
                "sensitivity, forming a box open to the front (beam)",
                "side. The position-averaged detection efficiency for",
                "full-energy alpha-particles emitted in the decays of",
                "implanted nuclei was 87%."
              ]
            }
          ],
